<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_2b95e537-b5ba-4d85-a04d-d1502138922a" outputclass="ncc-clause"><sptc>B2P7</sptc><title id="_333c7d83-84b8-4fe5-af71-391ff25de264">Legionella control</title><archive-num>2019: BP2.5</archive-num><subclause id="_e25626e0-eb21-4437-99d8-2b325b23d7ec" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_ae4e4162-5493-4525-9325-51db99e98fb7">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1334_0.4.0.xml#_92b3a3dc-59e4-425f-909b-d8eb03e6460a" id="_cfc0a521-af20-43e3-ac50-537034d25a8d" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">Heated water</xref> must be stored and delivered under conditions which avoid the likelihood of the growth of a Legionella bacteria count greater than or equal to 10 Legionella colony forming units (cfu) per millilitre.</p></subclause><callout id="_026215fb-66db-4ed8-9725-7f2c7df108c8"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>A risk assessment should be undertaken for the control and management of Legionella in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1334_0.4.0.xml#_92b3a3dc-59e4-425f-909b-d8eb03e6460a" id="_462699f8-f604-47a4-bb30-bf71fd95dc24" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">heated water</xref> systems in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1180_1.0.0.xml#_41ac03c9-62e4-45df-84a3-8f31abb6b147" id="_6236bbe2-d63a-461e-b472-1bee011731b5" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">aged care</xref>, <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1333_0.4.0.xml#_1f5fbee8-584a-4244-9286-ebf9d8ebb04a" id="_7038a643-bb01-4969-bf19-d23d4f9179c0" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">health-care</xref> and other similar facilities which likely contain immunocompromised occupants.</p></callout></clause>